extends ../ui_layout

block content

  .ui.text.container
    //-        
        br
        h3 Now you get to explore the LearnLove.Life timeline! You can read what others have posted, respond, or make your own posts.
        br
        h3 Before We Start

        p
            img.ui.avatar.image(src='/profile_pictures/user55.jpg')
            <b>Dylan Goldstein</b> just moved into town and is new in school. He loves to draw comics and spends most of recess sitting by himself drawing in his sketchbook.

        p Some of Dylan’s classmates have started to make fun of him at school. Last week, 
            img.ui.avatar.image(src='/profile_pictures/user66.jpeg')
            <b>Keegan Scott</b> secretly took a picture of Dylan’s sketchbook. She posted the photo on social media with a mean comment. Since then, Keegan’s friends 
            img.ui.avatar.image(src='/profile_pictures/user5.jpeg')
            <b>Ella Sroni</b> and 
            img.ui.avatar.image(src='/profile_pictures/user64.jpg')
            <b>Breana Summers</b> have also been making fun of Dylan on social media.

        .ui.info.message
            p Now, let’s apply what you have learned! Try to spot and respond to cyberbullying posts or comments on the LearnLove.Life timeline. When you get to the bottom of the page, click “Continue” to move to the next part of the lesson.
    //-h3 Click Let's Go!

    //-a(href='javascript:void(0);', onclick='javascript:startIntro();')
        .ui.big.green.labeled.icon.button
            i.rocket.icon
            |   Got it!
    br
    br
    br
    block scripts
      script().
        $(window).on("load", function() {startIntro()});
        function startIntro(){
            var intro = introJs().setOptions({ 'hidePrev': true, 'hideNext': true, 'exitOnOverlayClick': false, 'showStepNumbers':false, 'scrollToElement':true, 'doneLabel':'Done &#10003' });
              intro.setOptions({
                steps: [
                  { 
                    intro: "Now you get to explore the TestDrive timeline! You can read and respond to what others have posted, or make your own posts."
                  },
                  {
                    intro: "You're about to see a social media timeline of Elena, a middle schooler. Imagine you and Elena are really good friends. She has a real account (elena_and) and a spam account (realmellie22) where she posts personal things to her best friends. You follow both of her accounts."
                  },
                  {
                    intro: "How are her two accounts different? Think about her audience for each and what she posts."
                  },
                  {
                    intro: "You can also practice creating your own posts - Imagine you’re posting to a group of your friends and family. Create a post that is okay for this audience. When you get to the bottom of the page, click “Continue” to go on."
                  }
                ]
              });
              intro.start().onexit(function() {
              window.location.href='/modual/presentation';
            });          
          };
        

